{
  "text": "I see, then, that it is, shall we say, when an individual reaches a very old age, then, it becomes apparent to him in third density that he's worn out. Therefore, he's not attached to this vehicle as firmly with a desire to stay in it as he would be with a good-looking, well-functioning one. Now, after the veil, the body is definitely an athanor for the mind. Prior to the veiling, did the body serve as an athanor for the mind at all? I am Ra. Yes. You may ask one more full query.",
